\par     The OpenSSL Project is a collaborative effort to develop a robust, commercial-grade, full-featured, and Open Source toolkit implementing the Transport Layer Security (TLS) and Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) 
protocols as well as a full-strength general purpose cryptography library.
\par 
\par pycrypto
\par     A collection of both secure hash functions (such as SHA256 and RIPEMD160), and various encryption algorithms (AES, DES, RSA, ElGamal, etc.).
\par 
\par pyopenssl
\par     A thin Python wrapper around (a subset of) the OpenSSL library.
\par 
\par kerberos (krb5, non-Windows platforms)
\par     A network authentication protocol designed to provide strong authentication for client/server applications by using secret-key cryptography.
\par 
\par cryptography
\par     A Python library which exposes cryptographic recipes and primitives.
